ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A great introduction to feminist theory, of course, particularly on the state. I would recommend it. I found the course difficult, but truly do think I learned a great deal and that it is important subject material.

I have recommended this course to other students here at the Divinity School. This course provides solid feminist theory in dialogue with other key theorist on power dynamics within the state and amidst states as it concerns citizens and non-citizens (rights/non-rights).

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Deepened my knowledge very much. gave me a good background to literature that is reference in readings frequently.

This course was amazing. I am in a different discipline/profession and this course helped me to deepen my theoretical framework in my own field. This course also opened me up to a new line of inquiry and research. My thesis benefited greatly.
